    "## Exercises\n",
    "\n",
    "See `exercises/README.md` → E09.\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Use `bootstrap_ci` to estimate the 95% CI of mean GC content across 100 randomly generated DNA sequences of length 1000. Plot the bootstrap distribution.\n",
    "2. What is the difference between the Bonferroni and BH corrections? When would each be preferred?\n",
    "3. Generate two groups from N(0,1) and N(1,1) with n=10. What is Cohen's d? How does it change as n increases?\n",
    "\n",
    "## Quiz\n",
    "\n",
    "1. What does \"bootstrapping\" mean mathematically?\n",
    "2. Why is `ddof=1` used in the variance calculation for Cohen's d?\n",
    "3. What does FDR control? What does Bonferroni control?\n",
    "4. Why is `pseudocount=1` added in `log_fold_change`?\n",
    "5. On a volcano plot, where do the biologically interesting genes appear?\n",
    "\n",
    "## Reflection\n",
    "\n",
    "*After completing:* Explain the multiple testing problem in plain English, using the analogy of flipping a coin 20,000 times and asking how many heads you'd expect by chance.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Papers Referenced\n",
    "\n",
    "- Benjamini & Hochberg (1995) "Controlling the false discovery rate." JRSS-B.\n",
    "- Cohen (1988) Statistical Power Analysis for the Behavioral Sciences."
